title: For Sale:  SMITH & WESSON / WALTHER SW99 - .40S&W – TRIJICON FACTORY NIGHT SIGHTS – (4) 12 RD MAGS – SAFARILAND LEATHER HOLSTER
postcontent:
Predecessor to the current Walther PPQ M2 and one of the most ergonomic handguns ever devised, this police trade-in was very lightly used and is in excellent condition both cosmetically and mechanically. Used as my personal home defense handgun for the past few years, I have run over 250 rounds of both ball and defensive hollow points through it at the range without failure. It is well-balanced and easy to get on target and shoot accurately.   

The SW99 was produced from the alliance between Smith & Wesson and Walther. The unique and ergonomic grip of the pistol was designed by the renowned Swiss match pistol grip designer, Cesare Morini. It has double/single action, locked breach type operation and features several safety elements including a loaded chamber indicator on the right side of the slide, a protruding, red-painted cocking indicator, and a drop safety.  Notably, the pistol lacks a manual safety; instead a flush, de-cocking button is placed on the top rear section of the slide, which when actuated, places the firearm into double-action mode. A close-up of the button is included among the pictures. The SW99 features an internal striker, as opposed to the classical external hammer. Its unique sear system allows a short, Quick-Action trigger pull. The frame assembly, manufactured by Walther, is high impact polymer with sure-gripping serrations and textured contours, and includes integral slots for accessories. Sights are original Trijicon Factory Night Sights that are still effectively bright. Manufactured by Smith & Wesson, the stainless barrel is 4 inch service length.  Extreme overall length is 7 inches; maximum height is 5 1/2 inches; maximum thickness is 1.15 inches at the disassembly bar, but the grip part of the frame is only 1 inch thick. Note that the mainspring housings / backstrap parts can be easily replaced (alternative straps not included) to allow shooters to adjust the contour of the grip frame.  

We are furnishing the buyer with a total of four (4) steel bodied 12 shot magazines and a Safariland Model 6280-84 (MSRP $130) leather holster, also in excellent condition. This mid-ride, Class II retention duty holster has an attractive black basketweave surface.

With a full, 70 round compliment on-hand, the PPS-43C offers substantial firepower in a compact and handy platform. It is a natural candidate for a SBR conversion (subject to NFA compliance). title: For Sale:  Franchi Paratrooper Takedown .22 MINT!
postcontent:
This is a very unique item: For a very short time, Luigi Franchi, the famed shotgun maker from Brescia, made a very limited amt of .22 rifles called the Para Takedown. It was to commemorate Italian Paratroopers and was made in very small numbers, something in the neighborhood of either 500 or 3000, depending on which source you subscribed to. It is a tube fed, 10 rounder, semi auto .22 rifle made to take down and stored in a well made canvas case with accessories and sling. It is known to be very accurate, VERY VERY RARE, and very collectible.
Well, this one is pristine, mint, in un-fired, new in box condition.
Even the papers and tag are included along with the outer shipping carton as well as the original canvas case.
This is truly a time travel item.
For those that are lucky enough to qualify for a Class III suppressor, this is already threaded at 1/2-20, same as the CZ 452, or you can get an adapter and converted it to the common 1/2-28 threading for the typical American made suppressor/muzzle brakes device.

SOLD.

IL Concealed carry (CCW) classes now available.

Guns/ammo/holster available for use if needed, extra fees apply. 

IL CCW requires 16 hours of training, the first 8 hours may be grandfathered in with other training or military service.  Contact us for more details.

Also Firearms handling-  Dry fire practice (training with unloaded gun) dry fire drawing from concealment, live fire practice and live fire qualification.
Qualification consists of 10 rounds each at 5, 7, 10 yards on a large silhouette  B-27 target (32"x45").

There are no restrictions on the caliber or type of handgun used for qualification.

This includes a 12 gun rifle safe, that has additional space in the center for three shelves to hold ammo, mags, etc, plus three extra bins that mount to the doors for extra storage as well. I really liked these extra feature when I bought it, and I liked that this safe has twin locks on the rifle safe rather than the single that Stackon was known for at the time. I also bolted the add on pistol case to the top of it. The pistol case has three shelves to easily hold multiple pistols.

The (outer) dimensions of the rifle safe are 21" wide, 16" Deep, and 55" tall
The (outer) dimensions of the pistol safe are 21" wide, 10" Deep, and 18" tall
Overall height with pistol case mounted is 73"

The foam on the interior is kind of lightweight and the gun guides could use some more adhesive to stay stuck better, but it works just fine as is.

The outside are in good shape as well, except the left side has some scratches from living next to a shelving unit where I slid things next to it.

Includes 2 keys each for both cases.

I believe I found the closest match that Homak currently makes for comparison on the Home Depot web site, searching for Homak 12 gun, and Security Add on for the pistol case.

This safe also has mounting holes to allow you to mount the safe to a wall or the floor, I simply threw an extra bag of shotgun shot in the bottom and made it difficult to move and didn't bother bolting it down.

Its a great way to keep your guns out of the wrong hands and away from prying eyes.

Please contact me to set up a time to come look at the safe.
